Pattern- Design

Code-
var findErrorNums = function(nums) {
    let n = nums.length;
    let freq = new Array(n + 1).fill(0);

    for (let num of nums) {
        freq[num]++;
    }

    let duplicate = -1, missing = -1;

    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (freq[i] === 2) duplicate = i;
        if (freq[i] === 0) missing = i;
    }

    return [duplicate, missing];
};


Problem-
Implement FIFO queue using only stacks
Support: push, pop, peek, empty

Key Idea-
Use two stacks:
inStack → for push
outStack → for pop/peek

Concept-
Push → always go into inStack
Pop/Peek → take from outStack
If outStack empty → transfer all from inStack

Steps-
push(x)
Push into inStack
pop()
If outStack empty:
Move all elements from inStack → outStack
Pop from outStack
peek()
Same as pop but return top without removing
empty()
Return true if both stacks are empty
